        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39851",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Sorry, \"but do not work\" is not enough for reproduction.\r\nWhat are you doing, what are you calling, how does your adapter look like.\r\n\r\nNote:\r\nLanguage notices can be switched off... they are no failure, they are wished and available since 1.8 or earlier.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-06T11:04:03.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-06T11:04:03.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39854",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=danospv",
                        "name": "danospv",
                        "displayName": "Dan Osipov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Notice is not an issue in itself, but the Adapter is not executed. Here is the Adapter:\r\n<?php\r\nclass MyNamespace_Adapter extends Zend_Translate_Adapter\r\n{\r\n    private $_data = array();\r\n\r\n    \/**\r\n     * Load translation data\r\n     *\r\n     * @param  string|array  $data\r\n     * @param  string        $locale  Locale\/Language to add data for, identical with locale identifier,\r\n     *                                see Zend_Locale for more information\r\n     * @param  array         $options OPTIONAL Options to use\r\n     * @return array\r\n     *\/\r\n    protected function _loadTranslationData($data, $locale, array $options = array())\r\n    {\r\n\t\t\/\/ ommitted logic for filling in $this->_data\r\n    \treturn $this->_data;\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n    \/**\r\n     * returns the adapters name\r\n     *\r\n     * @return string\r\n     *\/\r\n    public function toString()\r\n    {\r\n        return \"MyAdapter\";\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nI call it using:\r\n$translator = new Zend_Translate('MyNamespace_Adapter', '', 'en');\r\n\r\n\r\nI was able to narrow down the issue to the following lines in Zend\/Translate\/Adapter.php:\r\n\r\n        $locale = null;\r\n        if (!empty($options['locale'])) {\r\n            $locale = $options['locale'];\r\n            unset($options['locale']);\r\n        }\r\n        $this->setOptions($options);\r\n\r\nAt the end of these lines, the locale is set to 'auto', but:\r\n\r\n        if ($this->getLocale() !== (string) $options['locale']) {\r\n            $this->setLocale($options['locale']);\r\n        }\r\n$this->setLocale() is executed, even though there is no translation data was loaded from the Adapter yet.\r\n\r\nLet me know if this helps",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=danospv",
                        "name": "danospv",
                        "displayName": "Dan Osipov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-06T11:23:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-06T11:23:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39857",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I can not verify your problems:\r\n\r\nYou are giving '' as content, so there are no data which are added.\r\nThe raised notices are therefor correct.\r\n\r\nWhen I change your call to give content like\r\n{code}\r\n$translator = new Zend_Translate('MyNamespace_Adapter', 'somecontent', 'en');\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nand add a var_dump within your _loadTranslation method, this var_dump returns the previous given \"somecontent\".",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-06T12:16:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-06T12:16:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39863",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=danospv",
                        "name": "danospv",
                        "displayName": "Dan Osipov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok, I see. This works because of the following:\r\n{code}\r\n if (!empty($options['content'])) {\r\n     $this->addTranslation($options);\r\n }\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nBut why is the content required now? This was not the case in 1.10.2, and I understand that 1.10.3 was a bugfix release, that shouldn't have changed functionality?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=danospv",
                        "name": "danospv",
                        "displayName": "Dan Osipov",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-07T01:45:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-07T01:45:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39869",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "A translation was also required before.\r\n\r\n$data was not allowed to be empty... we just added array handling which means that the old $data is now internally named $options['content'].\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-04-07T12:58:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-04-07T12:58:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/39870",
